Reasoning: The paper presents a novel encoding of Allen's Interval Algebra using answer-set programming (ASP) extended by difference constraints, which is relevant to the fields of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and programming languages (cs.PL). The Interval Algebra is commonly used in temporal databases (cs.DB) and scheduling/planning applications, which also makes these categories likely. The paper also includes a preliminary experimental evaluation, which suggests that machine learning (cs.LG) and computer engineering (cs.CE) may also be relevant categories.
